EP  - 1157
VL  - 59
IS  - 3
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12299
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract We systematically investigate the links between the digit ratio (2D:4D)?a biomarker for prenatal testosterone exposure?and two measures of individual risk taking: (i) risk preferences (RP) over lotteries with real monetary incentives and (ii) self-reported risk attitude (RA). We find that both the right-hand and the left-hand digit ratio are significantly associated with RP: Subjects with lower digit ratios tend to choose riskier lotteries. Neither digit ratio, however, is associated with self-reported RA.
ER  - 

